# Security Rules

## Hard Prohibitions — NEVER DO
- **Commit secrets or API keys** — no tokens, passwords, or credentials in any file
- **Modify processor credential handling** — any file that handles `apiKey`, `secret`, or `credential`
- **Bypass live-mode toggles** — the `is_live_mode` and `test_live_toggle` flags guard production access
- **Modify `aws/` scripts** without explicit instruction — these affect production infrastructure
- **Change `config/config.toml` defaults** — defaults ship to production; use env var overrides instead
- **Create unsigned commits** — GPG signing is required for all commits

## High-Risk Paths
| Path | Risk |
|------|------|
| `src/entryPoints/` | Auth routing and session bootstrap — any change can break login/logout flows |
| `src/Recoils/` | Global state atoms — changes propagate to every screen reading those atoms |
| Any file with `apiKey`, `secret`, `credential` | Processor credentials — never log or expose |
| `config/config.toml` | Feature flag defaults — unintended flag flips affect all users |
| `aws/` | Deployment and infrastructure scripts |

## Before Touching High-Risk Paths
1. Re-read the task to confirm it requires touching these paths
2. State the exact change and why it is necessary
3. Ensure no credentials will be logged or exposed
4. Verify auth flows still work after any `entryPoints/` change

## Reporting
If you encounter a potential security issue while working on a task, stop and report it
before proceeding. Do not attempt to silently fix security issues as part of an unrelated task.
